Derived by applying decode login on Quantity, Tax, LineItemTaxAmount columns of MsOrder-Materialized DeltaStream files coming from upstream source cornerstone and of Asimov.v4.Cll file coming from upstream source cornerstone and ExchangeRateAmt column from EDLS source provided by Store Business Team.

Derived by applying decode logic on UnitsSold coming from FactRevenue present in UDPMLGCS DataMart and ServiceLineName,FullName,MasterSite,SolutionType,DataSourceName,BusinessSegment & ProductFamily columns from DimServiceLine, DimSupportQueue, DimVendorSite, DimSolutionType, DimDataSource, DimSupportQueue & DimSupportAreaPath tables coming from UDP Consumer within SA&DP.
Logic: If ~(lower('DimServiceLine.ServiceLineName').like('%smb%'))
       and ~(lower('DimSupportQueue.FullName').like('%smb%'))
       and ~(lower('DimVendorSite.MasterSite').isin('wcs', 'web sales support'))
       and (lower('DimSolutionType.SolutionType').isin('product'))
       and (col('m.UnitsSold')> -1)
       and ~(lower('DimDataSource.DataSourceName').isin('chinasmb'))
	   then HardCoded as "Store"
	   Else If lower('DimSupportQueue.BusinessSegment')=='mast'
	   then HardCoded as 'Advertiser'
	   Else If lower('DimSupportAreaPath.ProductFamily')=='microsoft 365 consumer retention'
       then HardCoded as 'SaveDesk' 
       Otherwise HardCoded as 'Unspecified' gives BusinessSegment
Logic 2: BusinessSegment joined with DimBusinessSegmentUnit by BusinessSegment from both tables and selected BusinessSegmentUnitKey
